ws/front/archives/2017/12/25/2003684599 |archive-date=1 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[R.550 Magic|Magic II]]\n| [[France]]\n| short-range [[Infrared homing|IR guided]]\n|480 missiles obtained<ref name=\"sipri1\"/>\n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | [[Air-to-surface missile]]\n|-\n| [[AGM-65 Maverick]]\n| [[United States]]\n| Air-to-surface missile\n| (500) AGM-65's \u2013 (40) [[AGM-65 Maverick#Variants|65G]]\u2019s  \u2013 (235) [[AGM-65 Maverick#Variants|65G2]]\u2019s<ref name=\"sipri1\"/>\n|-\n| [[Wan Chien]]\n| [[Taiwan]]\n| Air-to-surface [[cruise missile]]\n| >100 missiles produced<ref>{{cite web |title=Wan Chien |url=https://missilethreat.csis.org/missile/wan-chien/ |website=csis.org |publisher=Center for Strategic and International studies |accessdate=6 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190406213724/https://missilethreat.csis.org/missile/wan-chien/ |archive-date=6 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Ralph |first1=Jennings |title=Taiwan steps up production of missiles to create asymmetric advantage over China military build-up |url=https://nationalpost.com/news/taiwan-improves-missiles-to-counter-china-military-expansion |website=nationalpost.com |agency=Associated Press |accessdate=6 May 2019|date=2018-08-18 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[TC-2A]]\n| [[Taiwan]]\n| [[Anti-radiation missile]]\n| variant of TC-2<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chaunren |first1=Chen |title=Taiwan's Ching-kuo Upgrade Complete, SEAD Role Next |url=https://www.ainonline.com/aviation-news/defense/2018-03-20/taiwans-ching-kuo-upgrade-complete-sead-role-next |website=ainonline.com |publisher=The Convention News Company, inc. |accessdate=20 April 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[AGM-88 HARM]]\n| [[United States]]\n| [[Anti-radiation missile]]\n| 50 AGM-88B obtained<ref>{{cite web |last1=DeAeth |first1=Duncan |title=US arms company Raytheon takes new contract for Taiwan missile upgrades |url=https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/3711706 |website=taiwannews.com |publisher=Taiwan News |accessdate=28 May 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | [[Anti-ship missile]]\n|-\n|[[Harpoon (missile)|AGM-84 Harpoon]]\n| [[United States]]\n|anti-ship missile\n|(183) AGM-84's \u2013 (60) [[Harpoon (missile)#Harpoon Block II|84L]]\u2019s<ref name=\"sipri1\"/>\n|-\n| [[Hsiung Feng II]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Hsiung Feng II |url=https://missilethreat.csis.org/missile/hsiung-feng-ii/ |website=csis.org |publisher=Center for Strategic and International Studies |accessdate=2 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402220035/https://missilethreat.csis.org/missile/hsiung-feng-ii/ |archive-date=2 April 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n| [[Taiwan]]\n| anti-ship missile\n| \n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | [[Bomb]]s\n|-\n| [[AGM-154 Joint Standoff Weapon|AGM-154 JSW]]\n| [[United States]]\n| [[Glide bomb]]\n| 56 <ref>{{cite web |title=TRADE REGISTERS |url=http://armstrade.sipri.org/armstrade/page/trade_register.php |website=sipri.org |publisher=Stockholm International Peace Research Institute |accessdate=19 April 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Paveway]]\n| [[United States]]\n| [[Precision guided bomb]]\n| 50<ref name=\"sipri1\"/>\n\n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | [[Targeting pod|Sensor pods]]\n\n|-\n| [[Sniper Advanced Targeting Pod|Sniper Targeting Pod]]\n| [[United States]]\n| Targeting Pod\n| 20 AAQ-33's obtained<ref name=\"sipri1\"/>\n|-\n| [[LANTIRN]]\n| [[United States]]\n| Targeting Pod\n| (28) AN/AAQ-19, (28) AAQ-20<ref name=\"sipri1\"/>\n|}\n\n=== Air Defense ===\n[[File:Tien Kung \u2161 Missile Launcher Display at Hukou Camp Ground 20140329b.jpg|thumb|Tien Kung \u2161 Missile Launcher Display at Hukou Camp Ground]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! style=\"text-align:center; background:#aabccc;\"|Name\n! style=\"text-align: center; background:#aabccc;\"|Origin\n! style=\"text-align:l center; background:#aabccc;\"|Type\n! style=\"text-align:l center; background:#aabccc;\"|In service\n! style=\"text-align: center; background:#aabccc;\"|Notes\n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | [[Surface-to-air missile|SAM]]\n|-\n| [[MIM-104 Patriot|Patriot]] [[MIM-104 Patriot#PAC-2|(PAC-2)]]\n| [[United States]]\n| [[Surface-to-air missile|SAM]] system\n|7 \n|receiving upgrade to [[MIM-104 Patriot#PAC-3|PAC-3]].<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.libertytimes.com/2012/new/apr/4/today-p2.htm | title=First Upgraded PAC-3 Battery Is Based At Nang Kang | publisher=Liberty Times | date=2012-04-04 | accessdate=2012-04-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120403220833/http://libertytimes.com.tw/2012/new/apr/4/today-p2.htm | archive-date=2012-04-03 | url-status=live }}</ref> 264 additional PAC-3 interceptors delivered in 2011, 122 PAC-3 interceptors delivered in 2015.<ref name=\"sipri1\"/>\n|-\n| [[Sky Bow]]\n| [[Taiwan]]\n| [[Surface-to-air missile|SAM]] system \n|6\n|[[Sky Bow I]] replaced by the [[Sky Bow III]] missiles in 2015\n|-\n|[[MIM-23 HAWK]]\n| [[United States]]\n|[[Surface-to-air missile|SAM]] system\n|19<ref name=\"sipri1\"/>\n|\n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | [[Anti-aircraft warfare|Anti-aircraft artillery]]\n|-\n|[[Oerlikon GDF|Skyguard]]\n| [[Switzerland]]  \n|towed anti-aircraft gun\n|24\n| twin gun, 35mm rounds\n|-\n|[[RIM-7 Sea Sparrow]]\n| [[United States]]\n|[[Surface-to-air missile|SAM]] system\n|500 missiles\n| used on towed launcher as part of the [[Oerlikon GDF|Skyguard System]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/taiwan/archives/2012/07/25/2003538591 |title=Hundreds of missiles placed 'on hold' as Taiwan awaits US  |access-date=2018-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181006195529/http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/taiwan/archives/2012/07/25/2003538591 |archive-date=2018-10-06 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n! sty