ds\n|-\n|[[RIM-7 Sea Sparrow]]\n| [[United States]]\n|[[Surface-to-air missile|SAM]] system\n|500 missiles\n| used on towed launcher as part of the [[Oerlikon GDF|Skyguard System]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/taiwan/archives/2012/07/25/2003538591 |title=Hundreds of missiles placed 'on hold' as Taiwan awaits US  |access-date=2018-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181006195529/http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/taiwan/archives/2012/07/25/2003538591 |archive-date=2018-10-06 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | Sensors (independent of SAM batteries)\n|-\n|[[AN/FPS-117]]\n| [[United States]]  \n| Fixed Phased Array Long-Range Radar System\n| 7<ref name=\"AFP 2002\" />\n| Primary battlespace management radar<ref>{{cite web |last1=Zhezheng |first1=Hong |title=The Air Force admits that the Army's war management radars cannot detect early warning drone threats |url=https://udn.com/news/story/10930/4141695 |website=udn.com |publisher=United Daily News |accessdate=25 January 2020}}</ref> Acquired in 2002.<ref name=\"AFP 2002\" />\n|-\n|[[AN/TPS-117]]\n| [[United States]]  \n| Mobile Phased Array Long-Range Radar System\n| 4<ref name=\"AFP 2002\" />\n| Acquired in 2002.<ref name=\"AFP 2002\">{{cite web |agency=AFP |title=Taiwan To Receive Early-Warning Radars From US: Jane's |url=http://www.spacedaily.com/news/bmdo-02o.html |website=www.spacedaily.com |publisher=Space Daily |accessdate=25 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[PAVE PAWS]]\n| [[United States]]  \n| Early warning radar system\n| 1\n| \n|-\n|}\n\n==ROCAF Squadron emblems==\n<gallery>\nFile:ROCAF34mark.png|<center>\"Black Bat\". 34th Squadron</center>\nFile:ROCAF35mark.png|<center>\"Black Cat\". 35th Squadron</center>\nFile:12SQ.png|<center> \"Tiger Gazer\". 12th Tactical Reconnaissance Squadron</center>\n</gallery>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Development of Chinese Nationalist air force (1937\u201345)]]\n* [[Central Aircraft Manufacturing Company]], also known as CAMCO\n* [[Flying Tigers]]\n* [[Black Bat Squadron]]\n* [[Black Cat Squadron]]\n* [[21st Fighter Squadron]]\n* [[Republic of China Air Force Academy]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20141019030508/http://enweb.afats.khc.edu.tw/bin/home.php Air Force Institute of Technology]\n* [[Republic of China Air Force Museum]]\n* [[Ministry of National Defense (Republic of China)]]\n* [[Republic of China Armed Forces]]\n** [[Republic of China Army]]\n** [[Republic of China Navy]]\n*** [[Republic of China Marine Corps]]\n** [[Republic of China Military Police]]\n* [[People's Liberation Army Air Force]]\n* [[Political status of Taiwan]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|Air force of the Republic of China}}\n{{wikisource|Air Force Uniforms Act}}\n* [http://air.mnd.gov.tw/English/ ROCAF website] \n* [http://www.mnd.gov.tw/eng/discover/aircraft.htm ROC active aircraft] {{in lang|en}}\n\n{{-}}\n{{ROC Military}}\n{{Republic of China Air Force}}\n{{air forces}}\n\n[[Category:Republic of China Air Force| ]]\n[[Category:Military units and formations established in 1920]]\n", "name_user": "Horse Eye Jack", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eArmament", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republic_of_China_Air_Force"}
{"title_page": "Guangzhou", "text_new": "{{Other uses}}\n{{hatnote|\"{{lang|zh-Hant|\u5ee3\u5dde|italic=no}}\" redirects here. For the South Korean city with the similar [[Hanja]] spelling {{lang|ko-Hant|\u5ee3\u5dde|italic=no}}, see [[Gwangju, Gyeonggi]].}}\n{{hatnote|For other places with same name \"Canton\", see [[Canton (disambiguation)|Canton]].}}\n{{stack begin}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = {{raise|0.2em|Guangzhou}}\n| official_name                   = <!-- Official name in English if different from 'name' -->\n| other_name                      = Canton; Kwangchow\n| native_name                     = {{lower|0.1em|\u5e7f\u5dde\u5e02}}\n| native_name_lang = zh-Hans\n| nicknames                        = City of Rams, City of Flowers, Suicheng, [[#Names|others]]\n| settlement_type                 = [[Prefecture-level city|Prefecture-level]] and [[Sub-provincial city]]\n| image_skyline                   = {{Photomontage\n| photo1a                   = Guangzhou twin towers.jpg\n| photo2a                   = Guangzhou montage.png\n| color_border              = white\n| color                     = white\n| size                      = 270\n| foot_montage              = \n}}\n| image_caption                   = From top: [[Guangzhou Twin Towers]], [[Tianhe District|Tianhe]] CBD, the [[Canton Tower]] and [[Chigang Pagoda]], [[Haizhu Bridge]], [[Sun Yat-sen Memorial Hall (Guangzhou)|Sun Yat-sen Memorial Hall]], the [[The Legend of Five Goats|Five Goat Statue]] and [[Zhenhai Tower (Guangzhou)|Zhenhai Tower]] in [[Yuexiu Park]], and [[Sacred Heart Cathedral of Guangzhou|Sacred Heart Cathedral]].\n| image_map                       = {{maplink|frame=yes|plain=yes|type=shape|stroke-width=2|stroke-color=#000000|zoom=7|frame-lat=23.132|frame-long=113.6}}\n| image_map1                      = Guangdong subdivisions - Guangzhou.svg\n| map_caption1                    = Location of Guangzhou City jurisdiction in Guangdong\n| pushpin_map               