{"title_page": "Dragon's Heart Hospital", "text_new": "{{Short description|Temporary NHS COVID-19 hospital set up in the Millennium Stadium}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox hospital\n| name                  = Dragon's Heart Hospital<br/>{{lang|cy|Ysbyty Calon y Ddraig}}\n| org/group             = [[Cardiff and Vale University Health Board]]\n| logo                  = \n| logo_size             = \n| image                 = [[File:Principality Stadium May 3, 2016.jpg|225px]]\n| image_size            = 225px\n| alt                   = \n| caption               = \n| coordinates           = {{Coord|51|28|41|N|3|10|57|W|display=it|type:landmark_region:GB}}\n| location              = [[Millennium Stadium]], [[Cardiff]]\n| region                = \n| state                 = [[Wales]]\n| country               = \n| healthcare            = [[NHS Wales]]\n| funding               =\n| type                  = [[COVID-19]] critical care\n| religious_affiliation = \n| affiliation           = \n| patron                = \n| network               = \n| standards             = \n| emergency             = \n| beds                  = 300 (2,000 maximum)\n| speciality            = \n| helipad               = \n| h1-number             = \n| h1-length-f           = \n| h1-length-m           = \n| h1-surface            = <!-- up to h12 -->\n| publictransit         = \n| former-names          = \n| constructed           =\n| opened                = 11 April 2020 (scheduled) <!-- cite in article as well -->\n| closed                = \n| demolished            = \n| website               = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} -->\n| other_links           = \n| module                = \n}}\n\n'''Dragon's Heart Hospital''' ({{lang-cy|Ysbyty Calon y Ddraig}})<ref name = NameAnnouncement>{{Cite news|url=http://www.wales.nhs.uk/news/52401|title=Ysbyty Calon y Ddraig, The Dragon\u2019s Heart Hospital|work=NHS Wales|date=9 April 2020|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref> is an temporary hospital currently being built in [[Cardiff]] to help deal with the impact of the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Wales]]. It is the third of the [[NHS COVID-19 critical care hospitals]] set up in the United Kingdom, and the first in Wales. On completion it will have 2,000 beds,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/rugby-union/52024970|title=Coronavirus: Principality Stadium to be used as 2000-bed hospital|work=BBC Sport|date=27 March 2020|access-date=28 March 2020}}</ref> making it the largest hospital in [[Wales]], and the second largest in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-52228321|title=Coronavirus: Principality Stadium hospital taking shape|work=BBC News|date=9 April 2020|access-date=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Wales}}\n{{section empty|date=April 2020}}\n\n== Details ==\nIt is due to open on 11 April, with the first 300 beds becoming available. <ref name=\"NameAnnouncement\" />\n\n== See also ==\n* [[NHS Nightingale Hospitals]] - similar temporary hospitals in England\n* [[NHS Louisa Jordan]] - a similar temporary hospital in Glasgow\n\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{Coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|state=collapsed}}\n\n{{Hospital-stub}}\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|Wales]]\n[[Category:2020 in Wales]]\n[[Category:Health in Wales]]\n[[Category:NHS hospitals in Wales]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Temporary NHS COVID-19 hospital set up in the Millennium Stadium}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox hospital\n| name                  = Dragon's Heart Hospital <br/> {{lang|cy|Ysbyty Calon y Ddraig}}\n| org/group             = [[Cardiff and Vale University Health Board]]\n| logo                  = \n| logo_size             = \n| image                 = [[File:Prin